description: Manage outbound rules of a load balancer.

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule create
commands.syntax:
az network lb outbound-rule create --address-pool
                                   --lb-name
                                   --name
                                   --protocol {All, Tcp, Udp}
                                   --resource-group
                                   [--allocated-outbound-ports]
                                   [--enable-tcp-reset {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                   [--frontend-ip-configs]
                                   [--idle-timeout]
                                   [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
examples: az network lb outbound-rule create --address-pool MyAddressPool --frontend-ip-configs myfrontendoutbound --idle-timeout 5 --lb-name MyLb --name MyOutboundRule --outbound-ports 10000 --protocol Udp --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule delete
commands.syntax:
az network lb outbound-rule delete --lb-name
                                   --name
                                   --resource-group
                                   [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
examples: az az network lb outbound-rule delete --lb-name MyLb --name MyOutboundRule --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule list
examples: az network lb outbound-rule list --lb-name MyLb --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule show
commands.summary: Get the details of an outbound rule.
examples: az network lb outbound-rule show --lb-name MyLb --name MyOutboundRule --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule update
commands.syntax:
az network lb outbound-rule update --lb-name
                                   --name
                                   --resource-group
                                   [--add]
                                   [--address-pool]
                                   [--allocated-outbound-ports]
                                   [--enable-tcp-reset {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                   [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                   [--frontend-ip-configs]
                                   [--idle-timeout]
                                   [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                   [--protocol {All, Tcp, Udp}]
                                   [--remove]
                                   [--set]
examples: az network lb outbound-rule update --lb-name MyLb --name MyOutboundRule --outbound-ports 10000 --resource-group MyResourceGroup

commands.name: az network lb outbound-rule wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
